-- 2010-11-18T04:44:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-18/china-said-to-plan-sale-of-300-000-tons-stockpiled-rape-oil-to-cool-prices.html
China will probably sell 300,000
metric tons of rapeseed oil from state stockpiles next week as
part of government measures to cool prices, three people
familiar with the matter said.  The State Administration of Grain, which manages government
grain and vegetable oil inventories, may announce the sale today
or tomorrow, said the people, who declined to be identified as
